{
  "Hardy-Weinberg Equilibrium": "哈迪温伯格平衡",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is an r-selected (r-strategist) species?": "r- 选择的(r- 战略主义者)物种是什么?",
  "The 'r' in r-selection refers to the intrinsic rate of natural increase (r in the equation dN/dt = rN). r-strategists maximize their reproductive rate: short generation times, early maturity, high fecundity, small body size, and minimal parental investment. This strategy is favored in unpredictable or disturbed environments where rapid colonization matters more than competitive ability. r-strategists often display boom-and-bust population dynamics and typically exhibit Type III survivorship curves (high juvenile mortality).": "r- r 选择中的“ r” 是指自然自然增长的内在速度( 方程式 dN/ dt = rN) 。 r- 战略家将生育率最大化: 短一代时间、 早期成熟、 高生育力、 体积小和最小父母投资。 这一战略有利于快速殖民化比竞争能力更重要的不可预测或动荡环境。 r- 战略家往往表现出繁荣和萧条的人口动态,通常展示第三类生存曲线( 高青少年死亡率 ) 。",
  "What is a K-selected (K-strategist) species?": "K- 选择的物种( K- 战略家)是什么?",
  "The 'K' in K-selection refers to carrying capacity (K in the logistic growth equation). K-strategists are adapted to live near carrying capacity in stable, competitive environments. Traits include large body size, late maturity, long lifespan, few offspring per reproductive event, high parental investment, and high juvenile survival rates. They typically show Type I survivorship curves. K-strategists are more vulnerable to population declines caused by human activities because their slow reproduction makes recovery difficult.": "K- 选择中的“ K” 是指承载能力( 物流增长方程式中的K ) 。 K- 战略家适应于在稳定、竞争性的环境中接近承载能力的生活。 它的缺陷包括体积大、成熟晚、寿命长、每次生育事件生育的后代很少、父母投资高和青少年存活率高。 它们通常显示I型幸存者曲线。 K型战略家更容易受到人类活动造成的人口减少的影响,因为繁殖缓慢导致恢复困难。",
  "What is a population crash?": "什么是人口崩溃?",
  "A population crash (die-off) is the bust phase of a boom-and-bust cycle. It occurs when a population that has exceeded K experiences severe resource scarcity and environmental degradation. The crash is often dramatic — the St. Matthew Island reindeer went from 6,000 to 42 in a single harsh winter. Crashes can overshoot on the downside, dropping the population well below K, especially if the overshoot phase damaged the resource base and lowered K itself. r-strategists experience crashes more frequently, while K-strategist crashes are rarer but often more devastating to the species.": "人口崩溃(灭亡)是繁荣与萧条循环的萧条阶段,当超过K的人口经历了严重的资源匮乏和环境退化时,就会出现这种情况。这种崩溃往往非常剧烈,圣马修岛驯鹿在一严冬从6000头增加到42头。 坠落者在下坡会超速,人口大大低于K,特别是如果过度砍伐阶段破坏了资源基础并降低了K本身。 皇家战略学家更频繁地遭遇崩溃,而K战略家的碰撞则更罕见,但往往对物种造成更大的破坏。",
  "What is a predator-prey cycle?": "什么是掠食动物和猎食动物的循环?",
  "Predator-prey cycles are among the most important density-dependent population dynamics in ecology. The classic pattern: (1) prey increases → (2) predators increase (with a time lag, due to reproduction delays) → (3) heavy predation reduces prey → (4) food shortage reduces predators → cycle repeats. The Lotka-Volterra equations model this mathematically. The best-documented example is the Canadian lynx and snowshoe hare cycle (~9-11 year period), recorded in nearly 200 years of fur-trapping data from the Hudson's Bay Company.": "捕食者-捕食者-捕食者-捕食者周期是生态中最重要的依赖密度的人口动态之一。典型模式:(1)猎物增加  (2)捕食者增加(由于繁殖延迟,时间滞后)  (3) 重食减少猎物  (4) 食物短缺减少捕食者  周期重复。Lotka-Volterra 方程式以这种数学模型为模型。最有据可查的例子就是加拿大的林克斯和雪鞋兔周期(~9-11年期),记录在哈德逊湾公司近200年的毛皮掠夺数据中。",
  "In Yellowstone National Park, elk populations grew dramatically after wolf extirpation in the 1920s. Elk overgrazed riparian vegetation, which increased stream erosion, reduced beaver habitat, and decreased biodiversity. After wolf reintroduction in 1995, elk numbers declined and shifted their behavior (avoiding valleys), allowing vegetation recovery. A wildlife manager argues this shows wolves are the SINGLE factor regulating elk. Is this claim fully supported?": "在黄石公园,20世纪20年代狼灭绝后,驼鹿人口急剧增长。 驼鹿过度放牧的河滨植被增加了溪流侵蚀、海狸栖息地减少、生物多样性减少。 在1995年狼重新引入后,驼鹿数量下降并改变其行为(放弃山谷 ) , 从而得以恢复植被。 野生动物经理说,这说明狼是调节的SINGLE因素。 这一主张是否得到充分支持?",
  "Population regulation is almost always multi-factorial. Wolves provide important top-down density-dependent regulation (both through direct predation and the 'ecology of fear' that changes elk behavior). However, Yellowstone elk are also regulated by: bottom-up food limitation (winter range quality), other predators (bears, cougars), disease (chronic wasting disease, brucellosis), density-independent winter severity, and human hunting outside park boundaries. Research suggests wolf reintroduction was one of several concurrent factors in the elk decline. Understanding that regulation involves multiple interacting mechanisms — not a single silver bullet — is essential for ecosystem management.": "人口管制几乎总是多因素的。狼群提供自上而下、依赖密度的重要管制(通过直接掠夺和“恐惧生态学 ” ) , 从而改变蚂蚁的行为。然而,黄石公园也受以下管制:自下而上的食物限制(冬季质量 ) , 其他掠食动物(熊、美洲虎 ) , 疾病 (慢性消瘦疾病 , 布鲁氏病 ) , 密度独立的冬季严重性 , 以及公园边界外的人类狩猎 。 研究表明, 狼重新引入是燕子衰落的若干同时因素之一。 理解监管涉及多种互动机制 — — 而不是单一的银子弹 — — 对生态系统管理至关重要。",
  "A pest management specialist notices that a ladybug (Coccinella septempunctata) population in an agricultural field surges after aphid numbers increase each spring, then declines in late summer when aphid populations crash. The next year, an early frost kills 70% of overwintering ladybugs before aphids emerge. How would this affect the predator-prey cycle?": "病虫害管理专家指出,农用田里的一只小虫(Coccinella seeptempunctata)人口每年春天在虫数增加之后出现剧增,然后在夏季末当虫类人口崩溃时下降。 明年,早期的霜冻在虫子出现之前杀死了70%的过热大虫。 这将如何影响捕食者与捕食者之间的周期?",
  "This illustrates how density-independent events can disrupt density-dependent regulatory cycles. The normal cycle: aphids increase → ladybugs increase (lagged) → ladybug predation controls aphids → aphid crash → ladybug decline → cycle resets. The frost (density-independent) crashes ladybug numbers before the cycle begins, removing the density-dependent control on aphids. Without sufficient predation, aphids can explode, potentially causing crop damage. Integrated Pest Management (IPM) must account for these disruptions — farmers may need to release commercial ladybugs or apply targeted controls when winter conditions weaken natural predator-prey regulation.": "这说明了依赖密度的事件会如何扰乱依赖密度的监管周期。正常周期:虫子会增加虫的增加(滞后) 虫的先发制人控制虫虫子的崩溃 虫虫虫虫的下降 虫虫虫的周期性下降    循环变",
  "A conservation team is developing a recovery plan for the California condor, which was reduced to just 22 individuals in 1987. Condors are classic K-strategists: they don't breed until age 6-8, produce only one egg every other year, and have a 60-year lifespan. Despite a captive breeding program that has increased the population to ~500, the species remains critically dependent on human management. Why is the K-strategy life history a particular challenge for recovery?": "一个保护团队正在为加利福尼亚神鹰制定恢复计划,1987年,它只减少到22人。 Condors是典型的K型战略家:他们到6-8岁才繁殖,每隔一年只生产一个蛋,并且有60年的寿命。尽管一个将人口增加到~500的捕食性繁殖计划,但该物种仍然严重依赖人类的管理。为什么K型战略生命史是恢复的特别挑战?",
  "K-strategist traits make conservation recovery extremely challenging. At one egg every two years and 6-8 years to maturity, even a perfect breeding program produces population growth far slower than r-strategists could achieve. Each individual lost represents a proportionally greater setback. The small population is vulnerable to the extinction vortex: inbreeding depression, demographic stochasticity (random variation in births/deaths), and Allee effects. Contrast with Kemp's ridley sea turtles (r-strategist): protected nesting beaches and headstarting programs produced rapid population increases because each female produces hundreds of eggs per season. K-strategists require sustained, multi-decade commitment and zero tolerance for ongoing mortality threats.": "K战略特征使得养护恢复极具挑战性。每两年一个蛋,到成熟的6-8年,即使一个完美的育种方案也比R-战略家所能达到的要慢得多。每个损失的个人都是一个比例更大的挫折。小人口容易受到灭绝旋涡的伤害:抑郁症、人口随机性(出生/死亡的随机变化)和Allee效应。 与Kemp的ridley海龟(R-战略家)相比,受保护的筑巢海滩和启动方案导致人口快速增长,因为每个女性每季产下数百个鸡蛋。 K战略家需要持续、多年的承诺和对持续死亡威胁的零容忍。"
}